    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>without going all the way through to degree sum formula, like it's done in Mathlib, as it seems.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Mathlib is definitely not going through the degree sum formula here, you can search for <code>sum_degrees_eq_twice_card_edges</code> in the source to verify this. <em>Edit:</em> Maybe it's actually using some version of it for the edge version, but for the dart version of your lemma, take a look at <code>dart_card_eq_twice_card_edges</code>.</p>\n<p>It's a simple double counting argument, making use of Dart as an intermediate data type to organize the proof, but that's not strictly necessary (these ordered pairs of adjacent vertices).</p>",
